column18:
6 kayaks were tandem kayaks
bicyclists biked onto the start of the bar beach and then turned around back up the road
disturbances: child picking up snail, drone flying over bar
one person parked their car, then picked up either seaweed or nets, not directly on the bar but more to the left if you're looking at bar island.

Man emptied diet coke can.
1 child in a tide pool. 
Definitely seeing people coming back across the bar who had to have come off the island when I did my intial count.
A group of 4 people walked bikes onto the bar, 2 attempted to bike across. 
1 dog peed.
Woman left the bar carrying a little bag of clams and other shells.

the person with the kayak drove to the entrance, unloaded her stuff, then went and parked elsewhere. a few people came, looked at the sign, and left. There were a few babies being carried. The dog was with the kayaker.
Only observed for 30 minutes because Ken's field trip went long. I arrived at 6:00 and stayed until full dark, when I was the only person left on the Bar, which was at 6:30.
